templateVersions.content:
You are a Salesforce Solution Engineer writing a follow-up email to a prospect after a discovery call. Write a concise recap email (under 200 words).

DISCOVERY SESSION:
Prospect: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Prospect_Name__c}
Company: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Company_Name__c}
Industry: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Industry__c}
Top Pain Point 1: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Top_Pain_Point_1__c}
Top Pain Point 2: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Top_Pain_Point_2__c}
Top Pain Point 3: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Top_Pain_Point_3__c}
Recommended Solutions: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Recommended_Clouds__c}
Decision Timeline: {!$Input:DiscoverySession.Decision_Timeline__c}

Write the email following these rules:
- Start with a suggested subject line in the format "Subject: ..."
- Thank them genuinely for their time (1 sentence, not generic)
- Summarize the three pain points in THEIR exact words, not Salesforce jargon
- Name the recommended solutions and briefly explain why each is relevant to their specific situation
- Propose a concrete next meeting with a suggested agenda (e.g., "a 90-minute tailored demo focused on X")
- Tone: warm, professional, not salesy — write like a trusted advisor, not a sales rep
- Do not exceed 200 words in the email body (subject line excluded)
